+ Let’s make our homes incredible together! Follow for tutorials, tips, tricks and inspiration!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Philip or Flop  |  DIY Junkie on August 30, 2021 tagging @loweshomeimprovement. May be an image of 2 people, table and indoor.

node.text:
Brandon’s office is DONE! I’ve had the best time over the last few weeks creating an awesome and accessible space for him to work and hang out in (swipe for all the angles). Check out my stories (and highlight) to see how I made him an accessible custom desk and outfitted the rest of his office with other smart home products! This project wouldn’t have been possible without the generous support of @loweshomeimprovement, they have so many budget friendly home and accessible upgrades to make homes better for all! #LowesPartner #LowesGoals 
.
.
#homeoffice #homedesign #homedesignideas

node.text:
When your friend needs an office, you go build him an office! This feature wall (see stories for tutorial) that I built this weekend is the first phase of creating a functional and accessible workspace so that my buddy Brandon can do big things! Follow in stories as I finish out the space! 
.
.
#boardandbatten #featurewall #homeoffice #homedecor #walltreatment #carpentry

node.text:
The inside of the porch is DONE! Swipe for some more angles and the before! I’ve never built a porch before but I feel pretty good about how my first one turned out. 🙂 I want to thank everyone that has cheered me on in stories for the last few months and for my Dad who has spent hundreds of hours with me on weekends along the way! 
.
.
#porch #porchdecor #screenedporch #betterhomesandgardens #bhghome #homedecor #homedesign #homedesign #homeinspiration

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Philip or Flop  |  DIY Junkie on July 11, 2021. May be an image of standing and indoor.

node.text:
Porch lighting with a view inside! This weekend I got most of the transition between the porch and the house trimmed out including board and batten siding up top! (Don’t worry the yellow is just the primer color 🙂). After a few more pieces of trim I’ll start the screening process and Michael my mason will be back soon to finish the stone! Head to my stories to get the details on the lighting I picked and let me know what you think down in the comments!
.
.
#porch #homerenovation #diyprojects #diyproject #fixerupper #ceilingbeams #screenedporch #bhghome #homedesign #homedesigns #homeideas

node.text:
I built this y’all!! A lot of siding and trim went up this weekend and it is really tying everything together! Swipe to remember where we started a few months ago 😮 (and for porch fireworks). Head to my stories to check out my siding and trim tips and click that story bubble next weekend with more porch action to come! 
.
.
All the trim seen here supplied by @84lumber !
.
.
#backyard #porch #screenedporch #homedesign #homerenovation #homerenovations #bhghome #southernliving #carpenter #backyarddesign #lawn #homeexterior

For Father’s Day, I got to spend time completing my ultimate garage workshop space! [#ElkayPartner] I installed a ton of new tool storage, added thin brick on the wall and was lucky to partner with @elkay_usa to put in an ezH2O Built-in Filtered Water Dispenser! Now I won’t have to run inside 30 times a day when I am working on my projects. See my stories for more details! #ElkayPartner
.
.
#waterdispenser #garage #ultimategarage #workshop #toolwall #toolstorage #garagestorage #diyer #homerenovation #homerenovations

I visualized this fireplace in my head a few months ago and now it exists!! My custom concrete fireplace surround along with the awesome stonework of my mason Michael makes for a one of a kind structure that I can’t wait to see everyday out the back of our house! Let me know what you think down in the comments and head to my stories to see how it came together!
.
.

node.text:
The porch finishing details started going in this weekend and this is getting good y’all! #sponsored This project has my been my biggest ever and many of you have asked me about the process of taking on a large home renovation.
.
This week I published a blog post with my sponsor @discover that breaks down the process of planning and paying for a large home renovation, head to the link in my bio to check it out! We went with a Discover personal loan to help finance our porch because they can customize home improvement loans around your budget. With a same-day decision in most cases, no origination fees and flexible repayment terms, Discover helped us save time and money!
.
.
.
.
#diyer #porch #porchlife #ceilingdesign #ceilingbeams #homerenovation #homerenovations #homereno #backyard #screenedporch #screenedinporch #homedesign #homeinspo

The decking is in and this thing is starting to feel like a porch! I went with a composite decking in a light color because I want it to feel like a separate space from the house and not try to “match” the wood floors. What do you think??
This project would not be possible without my awesome partner @84lumber . All of the wood and decking in this picture is from them. Check them out for your next home reno project! #giftedmaterials 
.
.
